4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE STATE PLAN COMMITTEE; ADDING MEMBERS
5 TO THE STATE PLAN COMMITTEE; AUTHORIZING THE COMMISSIONER OF THE DEPARTMENT OF
6 LABOR AND INDUSTRY TO APPOINT MEMBERS TO THE STATE PLAN COMMITTEE; COORDINATING
7 THE MEETING OF THE STATE PLAN COMMITTEE WITH THE MONTANA STATE WORKFORCE
8 INNOVATION BOARD; REQUIRING THE STATE PLAN COMMITTEE TO COORDINATE WITH THE
9 PERKINS STATE PLAN IN THE WORKFORCE INNOVATION AND OPPORTUNITY ACT COMBINED STATE
10 PLAN; AND AMENDING SECTION 20-7-330, MCA.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 Section 1. Section 20-7-330, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "20-7-330. Creation of state plan committee -- meetings -- report. (1) (a) The superintendent of
16 public instruction and the commissioner shall each appoint three people from their respective advisory boards
17 to serve on a committee to review and update the 5-year state plan for career and technical education as
18 required by 20 U.S.C. 2323. Two members appointed from each advisory board must be educators, and the
19 remaining member appointed from each advisory board must be a representative of a business or community
20 interest.
21 (b) The commissioner of labor and industry shall appoint three people to serve on the state plan
22 committee as follows:
23 (i) one representative of the Montana state workforce innovation board provided for in 53-2-1203;
24 (ii) one representative of the business community; and
25 (iii) one representative of the labor community.
26 (2) At least four times a year, In conjunction with the quarterly Montana state workforce innovation
27 board meetings, the board of regents shall meet with the superintendent of public instruction, the commissioner
28 of labor and industry, teachers, students, labor organizations, businesses, and institutions or agencies involved
